                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/phys-232" class="program-course-title">
              PHYS 232 Heat and Waves (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-33543" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Physics (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Physics              : The laws of thermodynamics and their consequences. Thermodynamics of P-V-T systems and simple heat engines. Free, driven, and damped harmonic oscillators. Coupled systems and normal modes. Fourier methods. Wave motion and dispersion. The wave equation.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Hong Guo (Winter)                  </p>

    
